# Frontend ESLint Footguns

Follow these existing Backstage `eslint-factory` rules when editing frontend code. Do not change `.eslintrc.js` or disable rules to pass.

## No default / namespace React import

```tsx
// BAD
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import * as React from 'react';

// GOOD
import { useState } from 'react';
```

JSX runtime does not need React in scope.

## No MUI / Material-UI barrel imports

```tsx
// BAD
import { Button } from '@mui/material';
import { Add } from '@material-ui/icons';

// GOOD
import Button from '@mui/material/Button';
import Add from '@material-ui/icons/Add';
```

- Do not use `@mui/*/*/*` triple paths.
- Do not import Node builtins in frontend packages.

## Backstage package / import constraints

- No relative imports across monorepo packages — use the package name.
- Declare dependencies in the package `package.json` (no undeclared imports).
- Do not import `*.test*`, `*.stories*`, `__mocks__`, or `__testUtils__` from production source.
- Do not use forbidden or self-package import patterns flagged by `@backstage/eslint-plugin`.

## Lint before finishing

After non-trivial frontend edits:

1. Run `yarn workspace <package-name> lint` (or `yarn lint:all` if multiple packages changed).
2. Fix any reported violations in the same turn.
3. Do not change `.eslintrc.js` or disable rules to pass.
